pair.value: AS IO Apply Ref Onboarding Type Updates to Templates
Model to update Templates based on ref data update

output-exprs.el: originalAndNewTemplates:#"_a-0000e7fa-f829-8000-9c17-011c48011c48_3386020"( onboardingTypeCode: pv!onboardingTypeCode, productTypesAdded: pv!productTypesAdded, productTypesDeleted: pv!productTypesDeleted )

newTemplates:#"SYSTEM_SYSRULES_forEach"( items: pv!originalAndNewTemplates.newOnboardingTemplates, expression: #"_a-0000e40a-de32-8000-9ba8-011c48011c48_260165"( cdt: fv!item, fields: "onboardingProductTemplates", newValues: #"_a-0000e2ad-62e7-8000-9ba2-011c48011c48_75800"( cdt: pv!writtenProductTemplates, field: "templateId", value: fv!item.templateId ) ) )

a:acp.name: sppv
a:acp.a:expr: =#"_a-0000e586-af6f-8000-9bd2-011c48011c48_1364193"( templates: pv!newTemplates, username: pp!initiator, originalTemplates: pv!originalAndNewTemplates.originalOnboardingTemplates, includeObjectDse: false() )

annotation.text: We don't write the product update in the "audit" subprocess because we query the templates without nested cdts for performance
